title: Leaked 'Star Trek Beyond' Set Photos Feature New Alien Species
text:
Comments Some photos from the set of the movie in Dubai feature some new aliens, one of which has a pair of flippers as hands. 
Some new on-set photos of " Star Trek Beyond " have made their way online. The latest photos capture new aliens that will appear in the upcoming movie while also giving a look at the filming location. It seems like the upcoming film will introduce a lot of new aliens. A video from an Instagram user shows two alien species walking out of a room side by side with crew members. The body of one of those aliens is black and he has a pair of flippers as hands. He also wears a black costume and a pair of black boots. A photo from @startrekbrasil shows two other aliens on the set. Wearing formal suits, they look like humans who wear alien masks. A video posted by Huda A. Syed Muhammad (@hudaarif86) on Oct 14, 2015 at 8:31am PDT A photo posted by Jornada nas Estrelas (@startrekbrasil) on Oct 13, 2015 at 4:14pm PDT There's also a video which shows the filming location along with four trampolines and some actors jumping on it. Another photo features some actors filming a scene in a location which appears to be the Star Fleet Academy. Besides, Chris Pine was spotted on set, reprising his role as Captain Kirk. A video posted by @sduhair on Oct 13, 2015 at 11:08pm PDT A photo posted by Mark Carson (@carson1878) on Oct 12, 2015 at 7:51am PDT A photo posted by Jornada nas Estrelas (@startrekbrasil) on Oct 13, 2015 at 5:22am PDT Those photos appear to be the last sneak peaks that fans can expect as writer-actor Simon Pegg has announced that the movie has officially wrapped production. He uploaded on Twitter a photo of himself along with co-writer Doug Jung. "That's a wrap on 'Star Trek Beyond'! Writers, Doug Jung and Simon Pegg consider life after 'Trek'," he captioned the photo. That's a wrap on Star Trek Beyond!
